@*
    Policies tab (a.k.a. "Quick Setups").

    Per the PM strategy doc, this is a first-class product surface, not a settings
    convenience. Layout reflects that:

      1. ONE dropdown picks the active or previewed policy. "+ Save current as new
         policy..." is the last option, after a separator.
      2. A tagline + status line under the picker tells the user, in plain English,
         what they're looking at and whether it's currently applied.
      3. An outcome-bullet list is the PRIMARY explanation: "Files end up roughly
         half the size", "Plays on phones, TVs, browsers". Never tech specs at this
         level - those are for power users behind the advanced disclosure.
      4. A "Show technical settings" disclosure reveals the per-field diff table for
         power users / auditing. Closed by default.
      5. Footer with Apply / Cancel only lights up when there's something to do.
      6. Manage menu (...) top-right exposes Rename / Duplicate / Delete / Export /
         Import. Built-ins disable Rename and Delete.
*@

<div id="policiesPanel">

    <div class="encoder-panel rounded">

        <!-- Section title + Manage menu --------------------------------- -->
        <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-0 flex-grow-1">
                <i class="fas fa-wand-magic-sparkles me-2 text-primary"></i>
                Quick Setups
            </h6>

            <div class="dropdown">
                <button type="button"
                        class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary dropdown-toggle"
                        id="policiesManageBtn"
                        data-bs-toggle="dropdown"
                        aria-expanded="false"
                        title="Rename, duplicate, delete, import or export">
                    <i class="fas fa-ellipsis"></i>
                    <span class="visually-hidden">Manage</span>
                </button>
                <ul class="dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-end" aria-labelledby="policiesManageBtn">
                    <li>
                        <button type="button" class="dropdown-item" data-policies-action="rename">
                            <i class="fas fa-pen fa-fw me-2"></i>Edit details&hellip;
                        </button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button type="button" class="dropdown-item" data-policies-action="duplicate">
                            <i class="fas fa-clone fa-fw me-2"></i>Duplicate
                        </button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button type="button" class="dropdown-item text-danger" data-policies-action="delete">
                            <i class="fas fa-trash fa-fw me-2"></i>Delete&hellip;
                        </button>
                    </li>
                    <li><hr class="dropdown-divider"></li>
                    <li>
                        <button type="button" class="dropdown-item" data-policies-action="export">
                            <i class="fas fa-download fa-fw me-2"></i>Export to file&hellip;
                        </button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button type="button" class="dropdown-item" data-policies-action="import">
                            <i class="fas fa-upload fa-fw me-2"></i>Import from file&hellip;
                        </button>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <input type="file"
                       id="policiesImportFile"
                       accept=".json,.snackspolicy.json,application/json"
                       hidden>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Picker ------------------------------------------------------- -->
        <div class="mb-2">
            <label for="policiesSelect" class="form-label">Choose a setup</label>
            <select class="form-select" id="policiesSelect" aria-describedby="policiesTagline">
                <option value="" disabled selected>Loading&hellip;</option>
            </select>
        </div>

        <!-- Status line: "Now using" / "Trying out" + tagline + Recommended badge -->
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center gap-2 mb-2" id="policiesStatusLine">
            <span class="small" id="policiesStatusBadge">
                <i class="fas fa-circle-check text-success me-1"></i>
                <strong>Now using</strong>
            </span>
            <span class="text-muted small">&middot;</span>
            <span class="small text-muted" id="policiesTagline">&mdash;</span>
            <span class="badge bg-primary-subtle text-primary border border-primary-subtle ms-1" id="policiesRecommendedBadge" style="display:none;">
                <i class="fas fa-star me-1"></i>Recommended
            </span>
        </div>

        <!-- Outcome bullets - the PRIMARY explanation for non-experts.
             Heading flips between "What this does to your library:" (steady/drifted)
             and "Switching to {name} will:" (previewing). JS owns the text. -->
        <div class="mt-3 mb-3" id="policiesOutcomeSection">
            <div class="text-muted small mb-2" id="policiesOutcomeHeading">
                What this does to your library:
            </div>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0" id="policiesOutcomeList">
                <!-- populated by policies-panel.js -->
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Drifted-mode banner: "You started from X but customized it." JS toggles. -->
        <div class="alert alert-secondary py-2 px-3 small mb-3" id="policiesDriftedBanner" style="display:none;">
            <i class="fas fa-circle-info me-1 text-warning"></i>
            <span id="policiesDriftedBannerText">You started from this setup but customized it. Your changes are saved.</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Advanced disclosure. Custom styling — Bootstrap's btn-link defaults to
             link-blue, which clashes hard with the rest of the purple/dark palette. -->
        <div class="mb-3">
            <button type="button"
                    class="policies-disclosure"
                    id="policiesAdvancedToggle"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    aria-controls="policiesAdvancedSection">
                <i class="fas fa-chevron-right me-1 small policies-disclosure-chev" id="policiesAdvancedChevron"></i>
                <span id="policiesAdvancedToggleLabel">Show technical settings</span>
            </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Technical settings table - hidden by default. Styling mirrors the
             dashboard's .dash-table: small uppercase headers in text-secondary,
             thin bottom borders only (no harsh grid), subtle primary hover tint.
             Diff row indicator is a left-edge accent + bold weight on the changed
             value cell - no swap-arrow icons (noise) and no surrounding border-box. -->
        <div id="policiesAdvancedSection" style="display:none;">
            <table class="policies-table mb-3" id="policiesTable">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th style="min-width: 14rem;">Setting</th>
                        <th id="policiesColCurrent"  style="min-width: 12rem;">Value</th>
                        <th id="policiesColSelected" style="min-width: 12rem; display:none;">Selected</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody id="policiesTableBody"></tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Empty state: no policies at all. Built-ins always seed, so this only
             ever shows if config is wedged - kept for safety. -->
        <div id="policiesEmptyState" class="text-muted text-center py-5" style="display:none;">
            <i class="fas fa-wand-magic-sparkles fa-2x mb-2 text-secondary"></i>
            <div class="mb-1"><strong>No quick setups available yet.</strong></div>
            <div class="form-text mb-3">
                Save your current encoder settings as your own setup, or import a
                <code>.snackspolicy.json</code> file shared by another Snacks install.
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary me-1" data-policies-action="save-as">
                <i class="fas fa-floppy-disk me-1"></i> Save current as new setup&hellip;
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" data-policies-action="import">
                <i class="fas fa-upload me-1"></i> Import&hellip;
            </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Footer ------------------------------------------------------ -->
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-end align-items-center gap-2 mt-3 pt-3 border-top">
            <span class="text-muted small me-auto" id="policiesFooterHint">
                Edits to other tabs are saved as you go.
            </span>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" id="policiesCancelBtn" disabled>
                Never mind
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" id="policiesApplyBtn" disabled>
                <i class="fas fa-check me-1"></i> Use this setup
            </button>
        </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Row templates cloned per-row by policies-panel.js. -->
    <template id="policiesRowSingleTemplate">
        <tr>
            <td data-field="label"></td>
            <td data-field="current"></td>
        </tr>
    </template>

    <template id="policiesRowDiffTemplate">
        <tr>
            <td data-field="label"></td>
            <td data-field="current"></td>
            <td data-field="selected">
                <span data-field="selected-value"></span>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </template>

    <!-- Outcome-bullet item template. JS clones one per OutcomeBullets entry. -->
    <template id="policiesBulletTemplate">
        <li class="mb-2 d-flex align-items-start">
            <i class="fas fa-circle-check text-success mt-1 me-2"></i>
            <span data-field="text"></span>
        </li>
    </template>

</div>

@*
    Scoped styles for the Policies pane. Two goals:

      1. The disclosure toggle must read as part of the Snacks purple palette.
         Bootstrap's btn-link defaults to link-blue and clashes hard with everything
         else in the modal - so we ship a custom .policies-disclosure that picks up
         --primary from the global theme.

      2. The advanced table must match the dashboard's table aesthetic (.dash-table
         style: thin bottom borders only, uppercase small headers in text-secondary,
         subtle purple hover) rather than Bootstrap's heavy default table look.
*@
<style>
    /* --- Disclosure toggle ------------------------------------------------- */
    .policies-disclosure {
        background: transparent;
        border: 0;
        padding: 0.25rem 0;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .policies-disclosure:hover,
    .policies-disclosure[aria-expanded="true"] {
        color: var(--primary);
    }
    .policies-disclosure:focus-visible {
        outline: 2px solid var(--primary);
        outline-offset: 2px;
        border-radius: 3px;
    }
    .policies-disclosure-chev {
        transition: transform 0.15s ease;
    }
    .policies-disclosure[aria-expanded="true"] .policies-disclosure-chev {
        transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    /* --- Advanced table --------------------------------------------------- */
    .policies-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        font-size: 0.875rem;
    }
    .policies-table thead th {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        text-align: left;
    }
    .policies-table tbody td {
        padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        color: var(--text-primary);
        vertical-align: middle;
    }
    .policies-table tbody td:first-child {
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .policies-table tbody tr:last-child td {
        border-bottom: 0;
    }
    .policies-table tbody tr:hover {
        background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.04);
    }
    /* Diff row: thin left-edge accent on the FIRST cell + bold on the SELECTED cell.
       No row-background fill and no swap-arrow icon - both add visual noise that
       drowns out the actual change. */
    .policies-table tr.policy-row-changed td:first-child {
        box-shadow: inset 3px 0 0 0 var(--primary);
    }
    .policies-table tr.policy-row-changed td:nth-child(3) {
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    /* --- Dropdown action entry tint ---------------------------------------- */
    /* Tints the synthesized "Save current as..." dropdown entry so it reads as
       an action rather than a policy name. */
    #policiesSelect option[data-action="save-as"] {
        color: var(--primary);
        font-style: italic;
    }
</style>
